{"source_slug":"merrett-frey","target_slug":"jennys-song","target_type":"object.text","evidence_paragraph":"Merrett is despised by his wife, «Mariya Darry», and treated with disdain by his father, Lord «Walder Frey». Merrett considers his wife a shrew and his children worthless. He hates woods and especially «outlaws», whom he often drunkenly blames for having ruined his life. He is familiar with «Jenny's song»."}
{"source_slug":"merrett-frey","target_slug":"knight","target_type":"title","evidence_paragraph":"Merrett is unable to become a «knight» because of persistent headaches caused by a head wound in his youth. Merrett tries to prevent the headaches, which can bring blinding pain and reduce him to tears, by drinking «alcohol» throughout the day. When his headaches become too severe, Merrett rests in a dark room with a damp cloth over his eyes. Fond of «ale» and red «wine», he has gained the dubious distinction of being the biggest drunk in the «Twins»."}
